# ðŸš¨ CRITICAL SECURITY REQUIREMENTS FOR PRODUCTION ðŸš¨
# 
# MANDATORY FOR PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. NEVER store production private keys in environment variables
# 2. MUST use HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or Azure Key Vault
# 3. Implement HSM (Hardware Security Module) for escrow contract keys
# 4. Use separate service accounts with minimal permissions
# 5. Enable audit logging for all secret access
# 6. Rotate all credentials every 90 days minimum
# 7. Use SSL/TLS certificates from trusted CA (not self-signed)
# 8. Enable database encryption at rest
# 
# DEVELOPMENT GUIDELINES:
# 1. Change all default secrets and API keys
# 2. Use strong, unique passwords for database and services  
# 3. Use environment-specific files (.env.local, .env.production)
# 4. Never commit sensitive credentials to version control
# 5. Use different databases for dev/test/prod environments
